==Events== * [[193]] &ndash; [[Septimius Severus]] is proclaimed [[Roman Emperor]] by the army in [[Illyricum (Roman province)|Illyricum]] (in the [[Balkans]]). * [[475]] &ndash; [[Byzantine Emperor]] [[Basiliscus]] issues a circular letter (''Enkyklikon'') to the bishops of his empire, supporting the [[Monophysitism|Monophysite]] [[christological]] position. *[[1241]] &ndash; [[Battle of Legnica|Battle of Liegnitz]]: [[Mongol Empire|Mongol]] forces defeat the [[Poland|Polish]] and [[Germany|German]] armies. *[[1388]] &ndash; Despite being outnumbered 16 to 1, forces of the [[Old Swiss Confederacy]] are victorious over the [[Archduchy of Austria]] in the [[Battle of NÃ¤fels]]. *[[1413]] &ndash; [[Henry V of England|Henry V]] is crowned [[List of English monarchs|King of England]]. *[[1440]] &ndash; [[Christopher of Bavaria]] is appointed [[King of Denmark]]. *[[1511]] &ndash; [[St John's College, Cambridge]], England, founded by [[Lady Margaret Beaufort]], receives its charter. *[[1585]] &ndash; The expedition organised by Sir [[Walter Raleigh]] departs England for [[Roanoke Island]] (now in [[North Carolina]]) to establish the [[Roanoke Colony]]. *[[1609]] &ndash; [[Eighty Years' War]]: [[Spanish Empire|Spain]] and the [[Dutch Republic]] sign the [[Treaty of Antwerp (1609)|Treaty of Antwerp]] to initiate twelve years of truce. *[[1682]] &ndash; [[RenÃ© Robert Cavelier, Sieur de La Salle|Robert Cavelier de La Salle]] discovers the mouth of the [[Mississippi River]], claims it for [[France]] and names it [[Louisiana]]. *[[1782]] &ndash; [[American War of Independence]]: [[Battle of the Saintes]] begins. *[[1860]] &ndash; On his [[phonautograph]] machine, [[Ãdouard-LÃ©on Scott de Martinville]] makes the [[history of sound recording|oldest known recording]] of an audible [[human voice]]. *[[1852]] &ndash; At a [[general conference (Latter Day Saints)|general conference]] of the [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]], [[Brigham Young]] explains the [[AdamâGod doctrine]], an important part of the theology of [[Mormon fundamentalism]]. *[[1865]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Robert E. Lee]] surrenders the [[Army of Northern Virginia]] (26,765 troops) to [[Ulysses S. Grant]] at [[Appomattox Courthouse, Virginia]], effectively ending the war. *[[1867]] &ndash; [[Alaska purchase]]: Passing by a single vote, the [[United States Senate]] ratifies a [[treaty]] with [[Russia]] for the purchase of [[Alaska]]. *[[1909]] &ndash; The [[Congress of the United States|U.S. Congress]] passes the [[Payne-Aldrich Tariff Act]]. *[[1914]] &ndash; [[Mexican Revolution]]: One of the world's first [[Action of 9 April 1914|naval/air skirmishes]] takes place off the coast of western [[Mexico]]. *[[1916]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: The [[Battle of Verdun]] &ndash; [[Germany|German]] forces launch their third offensive of the battle. *[[1917]] &ndash; World War I: The [[Battle of Arras (1917)|Battle of Arras]] &ndash; the battle begins with [[Canadian Corps]] executing a massive assault on [[Vimy Ridge]]. *[[1918]] &ndash; World War I: The [[Battle of the Lys (1918)|Battle of the Lys]] &ndash; the [[Portuguese Expeditionary Corps]] is crushed by the [[Germany|German]] forces during what is called the [[Spring Offensive]] on the [[Belgium|Belgian]] region of [[Flanders]]. * 1918 &ndash; The National Council of [[Bessarabia]] proclaims [[Union of Bessarabia with Romania|union]] with the [[Kingdom of Romania]]. *[[1937]] &ndash; The ''[[Kamikaze (1937 aircraft)|Kamikaze]]'' arrives at [[Croydon Airport]] in [[London]] &ndash; it is the first [[Japan]]ese-built aircraft to fly to [[Europe]]. *[[1939]] &ndash; [[Marian Anderson]] sings at the [[Lincoln Memorial]], after being denied the right to sing at the [[Daughters of the American Revolution]]'s [[Constitution Hall]]. *[[1940]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Operation WeserÃ¼bung]] &ndash; [[Nazi Germany|Germany]] invades [[Denmark]] and [[Norway]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; World War II: The [[Battle of Bataan]]/[[Bataan Death March]] &ndash; [[United States]] forces surrender on the [[Bataan Peninsula]]. The [[Imperial Japanese Navy|Japanese Navy]] launches an air raid on [[Trincomalee]] in [[Ceylon]] ([[Sri Lanka]]); [[Royal Navy]] [[aircraft carrier]] {{HMS|Hermes|95|6}} and [[Royal Australian Navy]] [[Destroyer]] {{HMAS|Vampire|D68|6}} are sunk off the island's east coast. *[[1945]] &ndash; World War II: The [[German pocket battleship Admiral Scheer]] is sunk. * 1945 &ndash; World War II: The [[Battle of KÃ¶nigsberg]], in [[East Prussia]], ends. * 1945 &ndash; The [[United States Atomic Energy Commission]] is formed. *[[1947]] &ndash; The [[Glazier-Higgins-Woodward tornadoes]] kill 181 and injure 970 in [[Texas]], [[Oklahoma]], and [[Kansas]]. * 1947 &ndash; The Journey of Reconciliation, the first interracial [[Freedom Ride]] begins through the upper [[Southern United States|South]] in violation of [[Jim Crow laws]]. The riders wanted enforcement of the [[United States Supreme Court]]'s [[1946]] [[Irene Morgan]] decision that banned [[racial segregation]] in interstate travel. *[[1948]] &ndash; [[Jorge EliÃ©cer GaitÃ¡n]]'s assassination provokes a violent riot in [[BogotÃ¡]] (the ''[[Bogotazo]]''), and a further ten years of violence in [[Colombia]] known as ''La violencia''. * 1948 &ndash; Fighters from the [[Irgun]] and [[Lehi (group)|Lehi]] [[Zionist]] paramilitary groups attacked [[Deir Yassin]] near [[Jerusalem]], [[Deir Yassin massacre|killing over 100]]. *[[1952]] &ndash; [[Hugo Ballivian]]'s government is overthrown by the Bolivian National Revolution, starting a period of [[agrarian reform]], [[universal suffrage]] and the [[nationalisation]] of tin mines *[[1957]] &ndash; The [[Suez Canal]] in [[Egypt]] is cleared and opens to [[shipping]]. *[[1959]] &ndash; [[Project Mercury]]: [[NASA]] announces the selection of the United States' first seven [[astronaut]]s, whom the news media quickly dub the "[[Mercury Seven]]". *[[1961]] &ndash; The [[Pacific Electric Railway]] in [[Los Angeles]], once the largest electric railway in the world, ends operations. *[[1965]] &ndash; [[Astrodome]] opens. First indoor [[baseball]] game is played. *[[1967]] &ndash; The first [[Boeing 737]] (a 100 series) makes its maiden flight. *[[1968]] &ndash; Funeral of [[Martin Luther King, Jr.]] *[[1969]] &ndash; The "[[Chicago Eight]]" plead not guilty to federal charges of conspiracy to incite a riot at the [[1968 Democratic National Convention]] in [[Chicago, Illinois]]. *[[1969]] &ndash; The first British-built [[Concorde]] 002 makes its maiden flight from [[Filton]] to [[RAF Fairford]]. *[[1975]] &ndash; The first game of the [[Philippine Basketball Association]], the second oldest professional basketball league in the world. * 1975 &ndash; 8 people in South Korea, who are involved in [[People's Revolutionary Party Incident]], are hanged. *[[1980]] &ndash; The [[Iraq]]i regime of [[Saddam Hussein]] kills philosopher [[Muhammad Baqir al-Sadr]] and his sister [[Bint al-Huda]] after three days of [[torture]]. *[[1981]] &ndash; The [[United States Navy|U.S. Navy]] nuclear submarine {{USS|George Washington|SSBN-598}} accidentally collides with the ''Nissho Maru'', a Japanese cargo ship, sinking it. *[[1989]] &ndash; The [[April 9 tragedy]] in [[Tbilisi]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]n SSR an anti-Soviet peaceful demonstration and hunger strikes, demanding restoration of Georgian independence is dispersed by the [[Soviet army]], resulting in 20 deaths and hundreds of injuries. *[[1992]] &ndash; A [[United States federal courts|U.S. Federal Court]] finds former [[Panama]]nian [[dictator]] [[Manuel Noriega]] guilty of drug and racketeering charges. He is sentenced to 30 years in prison. * 1992 &ndash; [[John Major]]'s [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]] wins an unprecedented [[United Kingdom general election, 1992|fourth general election]] victory in the [[United Kingdom]]. *[[2003]] &ndash; [[2003 invasion of Iraq]]: [[Baghdad]] falls to [[United States|American]] forces;[[Saddam Hussein]] statue topples as [[Iraq]]is turn on symbols of their former leader, pulling down the statue and tearing it to pieces. *[[2005]] &ndash; [[Wedding of Charles, Prince of Wales and Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall]]; [[Charles, Prince of Wales]] marries [[Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall|Camilla Parker Bowles]] in a civil ceremony at [[Windsor, Berkshire|Windsor]]'s Guildhall. *[[2009]] &ndash; In [[Tbilisi]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]], up to 60,000 people [[2009 Georgian demonstrations|protest]] against the government of [[Mikheil Saakashvili]]. *[[2011]] &ndash; [[Alphen aan den Rijn shopping mall shooting|A gunman murdered five people]], injured eleven, and committed suicide in a mall in the [[Netherlands]].
